abstract_ts:
We perform a measurement of the $\ensuremath{	au}\ensuremath{ightarrow}l\ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{
u}\overline{\ensuremath{
u}}$ ($l=e,\ensuremath{\mu}$) branching fractions for a minimum photon energy of 10 MeV in the $\ensuremath{	au}$ rest frame, using $431	ext{ }	ext{ }{\mathrm{fb}}^{\ensuremath{-}1}$ of ${e}^{+}{e}^{\ensuremath{-}}$ collisions collected at the center-of-mass energy of the $\mathrm{\ensuremath{\Upsilon}}(4S)$ resonance with the BABAR detector at the PEP-II storage rings. We find $\mathcal{B}(\ensuremath{	au}\ensuremath{ightarrow}\ensuremath{\mu}\ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{
u}\overline{\ensuremath{
u}})=(3.69\ifmmode\pm\else	extpm i{}0.03\ifmmode\pm\else	extpm i{}0.10)\ifmmode	imes\else	exttimes i{}1{0}^{\ensuremath{-}3}$ and $\mathcal{B}(\ensuremath{	au}\ensuremath{ightarrow}e\ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{
u}\overline{\ensuremath{
u}})=(1.847\ifmmode\pm\else	extpm i{}0.015\ifmmode\pm\else	extpm i{}0.052)\ifmmode	imes\else	exttimes i{}1{0}^{\ensuremath{-}2}$, where the first quoted error is statistical and the second is systematic. These results are substantially more precise than previous measurements.
